(43, 17, 5, 50, 2, 6, 6, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Divine Glory and Equality', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine glory and equality with God. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Jesus had before the world, while Philippians 2:6 emphasizes His equality with God.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 66, 5, 9, 14, 'glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Glory and Worthiness', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory shared between the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize the worthiness of the Lamb to receive glory, reflecting the glory that Jesus speaks of in John 17:5.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 5, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'the glory which I had with thee', 'Connection of Divine Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine glory shared between the two passages. John 17:5 speaks of the glory Jesus had with the Father before the world was, while Hebrews 1:3 describes Jesus as the brightness of God''s glory.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 43, 17, 26, 26, 'manifested thy name', 'Connection of Manifesting God''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the act of declaring God''s name to the disciples. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' mission to reveal God''s love and presence in them.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 43, 14, 21, 24, 'kept thy word', 'Love and Obedience Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of keeping God''s word as a demonstration of love for Him. In John 17:6, Jesus speaks of those who have kept His word, while John 14:21-24 directly links love for Him with obedience to His commandments.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'manifested thy name', 'Understanding of God''s Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God. In John 17:6, Jesus reveals God''s name to those given to Him, while 1 John 5:20 emphasizes understanding Him that is true through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 2, 3, 13, 15, 'manifested thy name', 'Divine Name Revelation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s name being revealed. In John 17:6, Jesus manifests God''s name to His followers, while in Exodus 3:13-15, God reveals His name, ''I AM,'' to Moses, establishing a continuity in the divine identity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 2, 34, 5, 7, 'manifested thy name', 'Manifestation of God''s Name', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s name being revealed. In both passages, the act of proclaiming or manifesting God''s name signifies His character and relationship with His people.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 40, 11, 25, 27, 'manifested thy name', 'Revelation of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the revelation of the Father through the Son. John 17:6 highlights that Jesus has manifested the Father''s name to those given to Him, while Matthew 11:27 states that the Son reveals the Father to whom He wills.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 6, 47, 4, 6, 6, 'manifested thy name', 'Light and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of revelation, as both passages speak to the manifestation of God''s glory and knowledge. John 17:6 emphasizes the revealing of God''s name, while 2 Corinthians 4:6 discusses the light of knowledge shining in hearts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 7, 16, 17, 'whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee', 'Connection of Divine Origin', 'Both passages emphasize that the teachings of Jesus are not his own but come from God. This connection highlights the acknowledgment of divine authority in Jesus'' doctrine and mission.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 16, 15, 15, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Ownership', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son regarding divine knowledge and possession. John 17:7 states that all things given to Jesus are from the Father, while John 16:15 asserts that all things the Father has belong to Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 8, 28, 28, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me are of thee', 'Knowledge of Divine Origin', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding Jesus'' divine origin. Both passages emphasize that Jesus'' teachings and actions are rooted in the relationship with the Father.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 10, 29, 30, 'whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Divine Authority and Unity', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son. John 17:7 highlights that all things given to Jesus are from the Father, while John 10:29-30 asserts their unity and the Father''s greater authority.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 14, 7, 10, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Knowledge of the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father. John 17:7 highlights the knowledge of what Jesus has received from the Father, while John 14:7-10 discusses knowing the Father through knowing Jesus.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 17, 10, 10, 'all things whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Divine Ownership and Glory', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, highlighting that all things given to Jesus are from the Father. This connection underscores the unity and shared glory between them.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 7, 43, 12, 49, 50, 'whatsoever thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Command', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that Jesus speaks what the Father has given him. This connection illustrates the unity of purpose and message between them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 43, 17, 14, 14, 'the words which thou gavest me', 'Connection of Divine Words', 'Both passages emphasize the act of giving ''the words'' from God to the disciples. This connection highlights the significance of the disciples'' reception of these words and their separation from the world.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 43, 15, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Knowledge and Friendship', 'This connection highlights the theme of revelation and relationship. Both passages emphasize the idea of making known the words and actions of God, transitioning from servant to friend.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 52, 2, 13, 13, 'received them', 'Connection of Received Words', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving divine words. Both passages emphasize the importance of accepting God''s message as truth, which leads to belief and effective work in the believers.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'thou didst send me', 'Connection of Divine Sending', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine sending, as both passages affirm that the Father sent the Son. John 17:8 emphasizes the belief in Jesus'' divine origin, while 1 John 4:14 testifies to His role as the Saviour sent by the Father.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 20, 1, 3, 3, 'received them', 'Connection of Instruction and Reception', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving instruction. In John 17:8, the disciples receive the words given to them, while Proverbs 1:3 emphasizes the importance of receiving instruction in wisdom and justice.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 20, 8, 10, 10, NULL, 'Value of Divine Instruction', 'This connection highlights the importance of receiving divine words and instruction. Both passages emphasize valuing knowledge and understanding over material wealth.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 8, 40, 13, 11, 11, 'the words which thou gavest me', 'Understanding Divine Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of knowledge granted by God. John 17:8 highlights that the disciples have received the words from Jesus, while Matthew 13:11 indicates that understanding the mysteries of the kingdom is given selectively.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 58, 9, 24, 24, 'for them which thou hast given me', 'Intercession for Believers', 'This connection highlights Christ''s role in interceding for those given to Him, as seen in John 17:9. Hebrews 9:24 emphasizes His presence before God on behalf of believers, reinforcing the theme of divine advocacy.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 43, 17, 2, 2, 'thou hast given me', 'Connection of Divine Giving', 'Both passages emphasize those whom God has given to Jesus. The phrase ''thou hast given him'' in John 17:2 connects with ''them which thou hast given me'' in John 17:9, highlighting the relationship between Jesus and his followers.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 42, 22, 32, 32, 'I pray for them', 'Connection of Intercessory Prayer', 'This connection highlights the theme of intercessory prayer, as both passages depict Jesus praying for his followers. In John 17:9, Jesus specifically prays for those given to him, while in Luke 22:32, he prays for Peter''s faith, indicating a focus on strengthening his disciples.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 43, 17, 20, 20, 'for them which thou hast given me', 'Connection of Prayer Focus', 'This connection highlights the shift in Jesus'' prayer focus from His immediate disciples to future believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of those given to Him and those who will believe through their word.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 17, 9, 62, 2, 1, 2, 'I pray for them', 'Intercession and Advocacy', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' role as an advocate for believers. In John 17:9, Jesus prays specifically for those given to Him, while 1 John 2:1-2 emphasizes His advocacy for those who sin, indicating His intercessory role.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
